•	log to the server to check its resource utilization (task Manager, resource monitor), SQL services status, cluster resources status, cluster manager error log and event viewer in case of Failover Cluster / AlwaysOn issues
•	log to the instance and check the AGs state and synchronization status in AG dashboard 
•	check SQL Server error log for any errors or deadlock reports
•	check the server sessions and currently running statements, long running transactions, foglight alerts for long running locks
•	check mail box for any related alerts or teams for notifications from other teams 
•	check the instance state in foglight or AWS monitoring for current or recent load and utilization 
•	foglight blocking report 
•	foglight SQL PI for historical data on the performance of the server 
